  • Enum Constant Details

    • TELEOP

      public static final Modes TELEOP
      Drive-controlled. Tele-operated is intended for functionality that requires a driver to control the robot manually via some form of controller input.

    • AUTONOMOUS

      public static final Modes AUTONOMOUS
      Non-driver controlled. Autonomous is the mode category best suited for things that you don't touch. Tele-operated is for driver control, autonomous is for a complete lack of that.

    • TEST

      public static final Modes TEST
      Testing mode. You can put whatever you'd like here, that's entirely up to you.

    • SIMULATION

      public static final Modes SIMULATION
      Simulation mode. This mode is intended for situations in which a robot is being simulated.

    • ROBOT

      public static final Modes ROBOT
      Robot main mode. This is the mode that's executed constantly, no matter what. As soon as the program initializes, we enter right here. Any Repeating Modes that are in the Robot mode executor are repeated until the program is fully stopped.
